# Auto Git Push

Remote: `https://github.com/harishhooli-coder/enterprise-ai-analyst.git` (branch: `master`)

## After every logical conclusion

When a task reaches a natural stopping point (feature done, tests green, bug fixed, refactor complete):

1. Run `git status` — if there are meaningful changes, commit and push.
2. Use descriptive commit messages (not generic "update").
3. Never commit `.env`, credentials, or `*.egg-info/` / `.pytest_cache/`.
4. Push to `origin master` unless the user specifies another branch.

## On 15-minute sync ticks

When woken by `AGENT_LOOP_TICK_git-sync`:

1. Run `powershell -File scripts/git-auto-push.ps1` from repo root.
2. If the script reports clean, reply briefly and wait for next tick.
3. If changes were pushed, summarize what was committed in one sentence.

## Script fallback

If commit message needs human judgment, commit manually then push:

```powershell
& "C:\Program Files\Git\cmd\git.exe" push -u origin master
```
